<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.918/248</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Italian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">De Martino</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-02">July 2, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I am in receipt of your
                            letter of June 16, 1931, in regard to <hi rend="italic">Il
                            Martello</hi>. As you are aware under our regime of freedom for the
                            press, it is extremely difficult to initiate judicial proceedings in
                            respect to published utterances of the nature of those which you quote
                            in your letter.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle,
                            Jr.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>